# Redux Studio — AI Photo Editor

## Project Overview
Redux is a browser-based AI-powered photo editing application built with Next.js 14 App Router and TypeScript. Users can upload photos, edit them with adjustment tools, and use AI features powered by Anthropic and Replicate. The app uses a credit-based monetization system where AI features cost credits that users purchase via Stripe.

## Tech Stack
- Framework: Next.js 14 App Router
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Canvas: Fabric.js
- Database: PostgreSQL (Neon) via Prisma ORM v5
- Authentication: Clerk
- Storage: Cloudinary
- File Upload: UploadThing
- AI: Anthropic SDK (chat assistant), Replicate (image models)
- Payments: Stripe (one-time credit purchases)
- Background Jobs: Inngest
- Caching: Vercel KV (Redis)
- Animations: Framer Motion
- Icons: Lucide React

