## Project Structure
- app/(auth)/ — Clerk sign in and sign up pages
- app/(dashboard)/ — protected routes (library, editor, settings)
- app/api/ — all API routes
- components/editor/ — Canvas, AdjustmentPanel, ChatPanel, Toolbar, HistoryPanel, ExportModal
- components/library/ — PhotoGrid, SearchBar, UploadButton
- components/shared/ — BottomNav, shared components
- hooks/ — useEditor, useCanvas, useAdjustments, useHistory
- lib/ — cloudinary.ts, anthropic.ts, replicate.ts, stripe.ts, inngest.ts, kv.ts
- prisma/ — schema.prisma

## Database Models
- User: clerkId, email, name, creditBalance, lifetimeFreeAI
- Image: userId, filename, originalUrl, publicId, width, height, size, format, embedding
- ImageVersion: imageId, url, publicId, adjustments (JSON), label
- CreditTransaction: userId, type, amount, feature, bundleId, stripeId
- CreditBundle: name, credits, price, stripePriceId, isActive

## Credit System
- Free users get 20 lifetime free AI messages for the chat assistant
- All other AI features require credits
- Credit costs: auto_enhance=1, auto_tone_balance=1, smart_color_balance=1, style_match=3, noise_reduction=1, clarity=1, heal=2, remove_background=1, generative_fill=3, chat_message=1, semantic_search=3
- Credit bundles: Starter(100/$5), Basic(250/$10), Pro(600/$20), Advanced(1600/$50), Enterprise(3500/$100)

## Code Style Rules
- Always use TypeScript with proper types, never use 'any'
- Always add 'use client' to components that use hooks or browser APIs
- Use async/await, never .then() chains
- All API routes must authenticate with Clerk before doing anything
- All Prisma queries must filter by userId to prevent data leaks between users
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling, never inline styles
- Use lucide-react for all icons
- Components should be small and focused — split large components into smaller ones
- Always handle loading and error states in components

## Key Patterns
- Protected API route pattern: always call auth() from @clerk/nextjs/server at the top and return 401 if no userId
- Image adjustments are stored as JSON in ImageVersion
- Credit deduction happens before the AI operation, refund on failure
- Use Inngest for any operation that might take more than 10 seconds

## Features & Tools

### Adjustments (Free — no credits required)
- Brightness, Exposure, Contrast, Blacks, Whites, Highlights, Shadows
- All adjustments range from -100 to 100, default 0
- Applied as CSS filters in real time on the canvas for performance
- Applied via Sharp server-side on export

### AI Adjustments (Credits required)
- Auto Photo Enhance (1 credit) — one-click AI improvement via Anthropic vision
- Auto Tone Balance (1 credit) — AI adjusts exposure/contrast automatically
- Smart Color Balance (1 credit) — AI corrects color casts

### Color Correction (Free)
- Vibrance, Saturation, Temperature, Tint, Hue
- All range from -100 to 100, default 0

### AI Color (Credits required)
- Style Match (3 credits) — transfers style from a reference image via Replicate

### Effects (Free)
- Sharpen, Vignette, Grain
- Range -100 to 100, default 0

### AI Effects (Credits required)
- Noise Reduction (1 credit) — via Replicate
- Clarity (1 credit) — enhance midtone contrast via Replicate

### Retouch (Free)
- Blur — soften specific areas using Fabric.js brush
- Eraser — remove parts of image using Fabric.js

### AI Retouch (Credits required)
- Heal (2 credits) — remove blemishes/objects via Replicate inpainting
- Generative Fill (3 credits) — AI fills selected areas via Replicate inpainting
- Remove Background (1 credit) — extract subject via Replicate, output PNG

### Transformation (Free)
- Crop tool — interactive Fabric.js crop rectangle
- Rotate/Flip — rotate 90 degrees, flip horizontal/vertical
- Straighten — align horizons
- Resize/Scale — input pixel dimensions, resample via Sharp

### File Management
- Upload: JPEG, PNG, TIFF up to 32MB via UploadThing → Cloudinary
- Free users: JPEG and PNG only, 5 uploads per day
- Export: JPEG, PNG, TIFF with quality control via Sharp
- Save to library or download directly

### Interface
- Undo/Redo — managed by use-undo hook
- Zoom/Pan — Fabric.js built-in
- Before/After — toggle between original and edited canvas state

### Performance
- Auto Save — save adjustment state to ImageVersion every 30 seconds
- Version History — list of all saved ImageVersion records, restorable

### AI Tools
- Conversational Assistant — Anthropic SDK, streaming responses, applies adjustment changes returned as JSON to the editor state in real time. Free users get 20 lifetime messages, then 1 credit per message
- Semantic Photo Search — image captioned on upload via Replicate, embedded and stored as pgvector in Prisma, searched via cosine similarity. Costs 3 credits per search

### Free Tier Limits
- 5 uploads per day
- JPEG and PNG only (no TIFF)
- 20 lifetime free AI chat messages
- No access to any AI features except the chat trial
- All non-AI editing tools are unlimited

